name: #11: "Compiling JavaScript ahead-of-time" by Oliver Medhurst and "TBC" by Rob Hough
location: Vulcan Works, 34-38 Guildhall Rd, Northampton, NN1 1EW
parking: St. John's Multi Storey Car Park

schedule.title: "Compiling JavaScript ahead-of-time" by Oliver Medhurst
schedule.description: Existing JavaScript (and TypeScript) is compiled just-in-time, compiled from source on user's machines, but what about ahead-of-time, compiled in advance like C++ or Rust? This talk will explore the pros and cons of this upcoming paradigm with real-world examples and working demos!
